field.value:
if we have a method like:
{{int Foo();}}
and interceptor doesn't {{Proceed()}} and doesn't set {{invocation.ReturnValue}} user gets cryptic {{NullReferenceException}} See http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8241907/castledynamic-proxy-nullreferenceexception-when-calling-method-of-a-proxy for example.
We should look into providing nice descriptive exception message here.
This most likely concerns value type {{out}} and {{ref}} parameters
